page.title: 16Wild life 2. Birds
page.content: The following{68 breeding birds}have been observed in the area: mallard,teal,tufted duck, goosander , shelduck, sparrowhawk, kestrel, partridge,pheasant,moorhen, lapwing, snipe,woodcock,curlew,common sand- piper, stock dove,woodpigeon,cuckoo, collared dove,tawny owl,green wood- pecker, greater spotted woodpecker, skylark,swallow,house martin,sand martin,crow,rook,jackdaw,jay,great tit blue tit,coal tit,marsh tit,long- tailed tit,treecreeper,wren,dipper, mistle thrush,song thrush,blackbird, redstart,robin,sedge warbler,blackcap, garden warbler,whitethroat,willow warbler,chiffchaff,wood warbler,gold- crest,spotted fly-catcher,pied fly- catcher,dunnock,meadow pipit,tree pipit,pied wagtail,starling,greenfinch goldfinch,linnet,redpoll,bullfinch, chaffinch,yellowhammer,sparrow,wagtail
